    "body": "Yes, I think we were the first ones to implement a DAICO at @windingtree, for us is a validation mechanism, either way the name does not matter. The cool thing about this is to decentralize the ownership/control of the funds raised ! ðŸŽŠ \r\n\r\nAlthough I like the MVM idea I would like to think on a solution that provides this control over an unlimited amount of time, in our case the MVM and what Vitalik propose there is an initial distribution and a period for the the \"validation mechanism\", but whats happens after? \r\n\r\nFor our MVM we destroy tokens that it receives and give ETH back, to continue the validation process maybe it can start a sell of the burned tokens in the past validation period?\r\n\r\nSomething like:\r\n\r\nToken Distribution -> Validation Period (tokens are burned, % contributions refunded) -> Redistribution Period (burned tokens, raise more funds) -> Validation Period again..\r\n\r\nSeems like a good model for non profit / open source projects.\r\n\r\n",
